@davidforrest1665 No argument there.
At least in some tripe you can get a good chuckle out of how ridiculous it was.
The only amusement I got out of the Acolyte was watching/reading the movie reviewers commentaries.  As well as some parody burns.

@stephenh5944As a kid  in the late 70s when I saw Star Wars it didn’t bother me but as I aged it hit me. Do all Wookies  just understand “basic?” (English) 

Han uses English to speak to Chewbacca and Chewbacca speaks to him in growls and grunts. Han apparently understands him so their relationship makes sense. I didn’t see the Holiday Special so I don’t know if all the Wookies understood Basic.  I have heard about the Empire enslaving Wookies did those Wookies get Basic or did the Empire just communicate with cattle prods and whips?

I have always just excused it all. (Or as Mystery Science Theater theme song says “It’s just a show I should really just relax.)

@Itisoverthere-rw It probably was malicious with how fans received Episodes 1-3.

It's obvious he put his heart into those and did such a great job of building the foundation of 4-6.  

As far as I can tell - people were scared by the relatability of the main character, choosing to hate the content instead of realize the dark side exists within them as well...
